# 🔹 Shared Libraries in Jenkins

## What is Shared Library?

👉 A reusable code module for Jenkins pipelines

---

## 🔥 Problem Without Shared Library

* Same code repeated in multiple pipelines
* Hard to maintain
* Error-prone

---

## ✅ Solution

Use **Shared Libraries**

👉 Write common logic once → reuse everywhere

---

## 🔹 Example Use Cases

* Maven build logic
* Git clone steps
* Code quality checks
* Deployment scripts

---

## 🔹 How It Works

1. Write Groovy scripts
2. Store in Git repository
3. Load in Jenkins pipeline

---

## 🔗 Example Git Repo

```
https://github.com/ashokitschool/my_shared_libraries.git
```

---

# 🔹 Pipeline Using Shared Library

```
@Library('ashokit_shared_lib') _

pipeline {
    agent any
    
    tools {
        maven "maven-3.9.8"
    }

    stages {
        stage('Hello') {
            steps {
                welcome()
            }
        }

        stage('Git Clone') {
            steps {
                gitClone()
            }
        }

        stage('Maven Build') {
            steps {
                mavenBuild()
            }
        }
    }
}
```

---

# 🔹 Key Concepts

| Concept            | Meaning                  |
| ------------------ | ------------------------ |
| Email Notification | Alerts team after build  |
| Parallel Stages    | Run tasks simultaneously |
| Shared Library     | Reusable pipeline code   |

---

# 🔹 Summary

✔ Email → Keeps team updated
✔ Parallel → Faster execution
✔ Shared Library → Clean & reusable code
